Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash 
and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Strip @Thyme{1/4%ounce} 
leaves from stems; chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings). 
Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. 
Halve, peel, and finely chop @Shallot{1}.

Toss Brussels sprouts on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of 
@Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon}, half the chopped thyme, and a pinch of @Salt{} and 
@Pepper{}.

Toss carrots on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and crisped, 
~{20-25%minutes}.

While veggies roast, pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; 
season all over with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add 
pork and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, 
~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Transfer to a second baking sheet.

> Swap in beef for pork; cook to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side. Transfer 
> to a cutting board to rest, then thinly slice crosswise.

Roast pork on middle rack until cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest, then thinly slice crosswise.

> Skip this step if not making the pan sauce!

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add 
shallot and remaining chopped thyme. Cook, stirring, until softened, 
~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 
@Fig Jam{1}, and @water{1/4%cup} (½ cup for 4 servings). Simmer until thick and 
saucy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until 
melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide Brussels sprouts, carrots, and pork between plates. Drizzle pan sauce over 
pork and serve.